---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Writing">
  <section class="py-20 px-6 md:px-12 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="font-mono text-xs text-primary uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-6">Writing</div>
    <h1 class="font-serif text-5xl md:text-6xl text-text-main mb-8">Notes from <em class="text-accent italic">the operational edge</em> of the AI era.</h1>
    
    <article class="bg-gradient-to-br from-base-light to-base p-10 rounded-2xl border border-primary/20 my-16 shadow-2xl shadow-primary/5">
      <div class="font-mono text-xs text-primary uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-6">Featured · Published on LinkedIn</div>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl text-text-main mb-6 leading-tight">The EU AI Act deadline is 4 months away. Here's the thing nobody is saying: <em class="text-accent italic">we've already solved this problem.</em></h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-text-muted mb-8 leading-relaxed">Risk classification? That's customer risk tiering. Documentation requirements? That's regulatory audit readiness. Human oversight of automated decisions? That's the daily tension between automation and manual review in KYC. The AI governance conversation is dominated by technologists and lawyers. What's missing is the operational layer.</p>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-primary">
        <span class="w-8 h-px bg-primary"></span> April 2026
      </div>
    </article>

    <div class="space-y-0">
      <article class="py-10 border-t border-base-light grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[150px_1fr] gap-6 group">
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-text-muted uppercase tracking-[0.1em] mt-2">Coming soon</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-text-main mb-4 group-hover:text-primary transition">The open letter I want to send to <em class="text-accent italic">my CEO</em></h3>
          <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">A meditation on what happens when the platform organization rushes toward AI without the invisible processes that turn activity into profit.</p>
          <div class="text-xs text-primary/70 flex items-center gap-2">In draft</div>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="py-10 border-t border-base-light grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[150px_1fr] gap-6 group">
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-text-muted uppercase tracking-[0.1em] mt-2">Coming soon</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-text-main mb-4 group-hover:text-primary transition">Five things KYC taught me that <em class="text-accent italic">apply directly to AI</em></h3>
          <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">Risk-based tiering. Policy-to-process translation. Human override by design. Documentation as the product itself. The decade-old playbook the AI industry is about to rediscover.</p>
          <div class="text-xs text-primary/70 flex items-center gap-2">In draft</div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>